aa1dd26c-9bb9-467e-8bb3-c07371e2d71b.d994026a-46ee-4b0d-8e1e-92dd76a2b2d3.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more
aa1dd26c-9bb9-467e-8bb3-c07371e2d71b.description=

Brocade commands ran\:
 - alicreate "${alias}", "${wwpn}"
 - alishow ${alias}


Synopsis\:
  This flow creates an alias for a WWN, with inputs for both in a paired list.  This can create multiple aliases in a single flow.

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Connect to HPNA (JRAS or HPNA)
3) Output success/failure and new alias info.

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
sanSwitch - IP of Brocade switch
alias_wwpn_pairedlist - alias1,wwpn1,alias2,wwpn2

Results\:
 flowOutput -new alias information, XML format.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}

aa1dd26c-9bb9-467e-8bb3-c07371e2d71b.e71026e5-89c2-47b9-be52-ab92951f533f.description=
Wanted to write a script that handles all the low-level operations and use-cases for CLU within HPOO.  This lets HPOO handle the entire request per higher-level inputs, including "overload" variables to the command line using variable-names within ${commands}.

Note\: Actual script example on sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab is running here\:  /data01/clu_direct/${scriptName} ${scriptArgs}

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) inputs\:
device_username	- username -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
device_password	- encrypted password -- NEEDS to be run against [mgmt_login] when writing TCL/Expect\!
runas_vendor	- HPOO needs override $tc_device_vendor$ to interpret prompts properly.  This to bypass CLU trying to get vendor information from HPNA rules.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}

Efficiency\:
checkForNull \= 0.016s
runCLU \= 10.241s
 - Connect to "sl7-owapp01.savvis.lab" and initiate Expect \= 7s
 - Init CLU \= 0s
 - Actual Commands against Router\: 3s
Cleanup .1s
